  "StockRole": "Mini-Sniper",
  "YangsThoughts": "The Pebble Crab started life with the Word of Blake before the Lyran Alliance and Federated Suns started buying it, and by 3080 it had spread to essentially every major military in the Inner Sphere and Periphery, which is a remarkable adoption rate for a 35-ton light. The reason is straightforward enough: putting two ER Large Lasers on a frame this small and keeping it functional requires fourteen heat sinks and leaves almost nothing else, but the result is a light mech that threatens targets well outside the range where most opponents expect to be shot at. It punches considerably above its weight class.",
